with version stable 0.1.10
with role    graphic
with trait   console server
with source  http://dev.gentoo.org/~spock/projects/uvesafb/archive/v86d-$VERSION.tar.bz2
with info    good 20120711
with info    last 20110305
with info    home http://dev.gentoo.org/~spock/projects/uvesafb/
with info    cite 'userspace driver for using VESA on non-x86 systems.
From the the website:
uvesafb is the successor of vesafb-tng.
Its main features are:
* works on non-x86 systems,
* the Video BIOS code is run in userspace by a helper application,
* can be compiled as a module,
* adjustable refresh rates with VBE 3.0-compliant graphic cards.'

build(){
./configure --default &&
make &&
make install DESTDIR=$DESTDIR
}
